<!doctype html>
<html class="no-js" lang="">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

    <link rel="icon" href="/assets/img/logo-32x32.png" sizes="32x32"/>
    <link rel="icon" href="/assets/img/logo-192x192.png" sizes="192x192"/>

    <title>UARMOR | Andrew Solomon - freelance full-stack developer</title>

    <link href="/assets/css/plugins.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/style.css">

    <%- include('./googletag.ejs') %>

</head>

<body class="v-dark dsn-ajax">


    <%- include('./components/preloader.ejs') %>


<main id="main_root" class="main-root">

    <%- include('./components/menu.ejs') %>


    <!-- ========== Header  ========== -->
    <header id="dsn_header" class="dsn-header-animation  show-box-shadow dsn-container section-padding v-dark-head">
        <div class="entry-header p-relative over-hidden">
            <div id="hero_image"
                 class="p-absolute dsn-hero-parallax-img over-hidden before-z-index z-index-1 full-width"
                 data-dsn-ajax="img" data-overlay="4">
                <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/1.jpg"
                     class="cover-bg-img transform-3d " alt=""
                     data-dsn-position="50% 50%"
                     sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"/>
            </div>
            <div id="hero_content" class="d-flex p-relative h-100 dsn-hero-parallax-title align-items-end container">
                <div class="content p-relative ">
                    <div class="intro-project w-100">
                        <div class="intro-title ">
                            <div id="dsn_metas" class="p-relative d-flex justify-content-between ">
                                <div class="metas has-separate p-relative mb-10">
                                    <span>Ecommerce website</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div id="hero_title">
                                <h1 class="title" data-dsn-ajax="title">UARMOR</h1>
                            </div>

                        </div>

                    </div>

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
        <a href="#page_wrapper" rel="nofollow" class="dsn-scroll-bottom"
           data-dsn-option='{"ease": "power4.inOut" , "duration" : 1.5}'>
            <div class="text">SCROLL</div>
        </a>
    </header>
    <!-- ========== End Header  ========== -->
    <div id="page_wrapper" class="wrapper">
        <!-- ========== Info Project  ========== -->
        <div class="info-project container text-center section-margin">
            <h2 class="title-h2 dsn-up">
                UARMOR
            </h2>
            <p class="max-w750 mt-30 dsn-up">
                <p class="mt-10">
                    I had the privilege of working on an exciting project—an online Ukrainian ammunition store. My responsibilities encompassed building the front-end components and implementing various features using Node.js, Vue.js, and MongoDB.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-10">
                    Utilizing Vue.js, I developed a dynamic and responsive front-end for the ammunition store's website. By leveraging Vue's component-based architecture, I created reusable and modular UI elements, ensuring an intuitive and seamless user experience. The website allowed customers to browse the product catalog, add items to their cart, and conveniently place orders.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-10">
                    In addition  I also developed a custom admin panel to empower the store owners to manage their inventory, update contact information, and oversee customer orders. This panel provided a user-friendly interface for the store administrators, enabling them to effortlessly update product details, track orders, and manage customer inquiries.
                </p>
                <p class="mt-10">
                    Under the hood, I utilized Node.js to handle server-side logic, ensuring smooth communication between the front-end and the back-end. MongoDB served as the database, storing product information, customer details, and order data, allowing for efficient retrieval and management of information.
                </p>
            </p>
            <ul class="intro-project-list mt-30 d-grid grid-md-3 grid-sm-2 ">

                <li class="dsn-up grid-item number-item">
                    <h5 class="title-list-project sm-title-block">≈Price</h5>
                    <p class="description-list-project dsn-auto"><b>2800$</b></p>
                </li>

                <li class="dsn-up grid-item number-item">
                    <h5 class="title-list-project sm-title-block">Stack</h5>
                    <p class="description-list-project dsn-auto"><b>NodeJs/MongoDB/VueJS/DigitalOcean</b></p>
                </li>

                <li class="dsn-up grid-item number-item">
                    <h5 class="title-list-project sm-title-block">Delivery time</h5>
                    <p class="description-list-project dsn-auto"><b>≈1 month</b></p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <!-- ========== End Info Project  ========== -->



        <!-- ========== Tow Image Popup  ========== -->
        <div class="dsn-container p-relative mb-section mt-sm-section">
            <div class=" d-sm-none h-50 top-0 background-theme"></div>
            <div class="d-grid grid-md-2">
                <div class="p-relative img-box-parallax before-z-index has-popup">
                    <div class="effect-popup before-z-index h-100"
                         data-src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/2.png"
                         data-caption="Caption #1" data-fancybox="_1" data-cursor="open" data-dsn-overlay="0">
                        <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/2.png" class="cover-bg-img" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="cap">
                        <span>Adding product</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="p-relative img-box-parallax before-z-index has-popup">
                    <div class="effect-popup before-z-index h-100"
                         data-src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/3.png"
                         data-caption="Caption #2" data-fancybox="_1" data-cursor="open" data-dsn-overlay="0">
                        <img src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/3.png" class="cover-bg-img" alt="">
                    </div>
                    <div class="cap">
                        <span>Product page</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ========== End Tow Image Popup  ========== -->

        <!-- ========== Parallax Image With Popup  ========== -->
        <div class="dsn-container over-hidden section-margin">
            <div class="img-box-parallax dsn-animate dsn-effect-down has-popup h-v-80" data-dsn-triggerhook="bottom"
                 data-dsn-grid="move-up">

                <div class="effect-popup before-z-index h-100"
                     data-src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/4.png"
                     data-caption="Caption #3" data-fancybox="_1" data-cursor="open" data-dsn-overlay="0">
                    <img class="cover-bg-img has-direction" src="/assets/img/portfolio/project5/5.png" alt=""/>
                </div>
                <div class="cap"><span>Home page</span></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ========== End Parallax Image With Popup  ========== -->

        <!-- ========== Paragraph  ========== -->
        <div class="container section-margin text-center">
            <p class="title-block dsn-text max-w570">
                Working on this project allowed me to further enhance my proficiency in full-stack development, particularly in building e-commerce solutions using Vue.js and Node.js. I take pride in my contribution to creating a secure and user-friendly online ammunition store that empowers both customers and store administrators alike.
            </p>
        </div>
        <!-- ========== End Paragraph  ========== -->


        <!-- ========== Next Project  ========== -->
        <div class="next-project section-padding p-relative footer-animate svg-animate">
            <svg class="dsn-separator dsn-separator-up  dsn-icon-main-color" width="100%" height="100%"
                 viewBox="0 0 100 10" preserveAspectRatio="none">
                <path class="path-anim separator__path" data-dsn-to="M 0 0 C 40 0 55 0 100 0 L 0 0 Z"
                      vector-effect="non-scaling-stroke" d="M 0 0 C 40 16 75 10 100 0 L 0 0 Z"></path>
            </svg>
            <div data-dsn-ajax="img" class="p-absolute dsn-hero-parallax-img transform-3d bg-container over-hidden"
                 data-overlay="4">
                <img class="cover-bg-img wp-post-image" src="/assets/img/portfolio/project1/1.jpg" alt=""
                     data-dsn-position="50% 50%"/>
            </div>
            <div class="dsn-container dsn-z-index-2 p-relative h-100 v-dark-head">
                <div class="p-relative h-100 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
                    <div class="intro-project w-100">
                        <div class="intro-title text-center">
                            <div class="metas has-separate p-relative mb-10">
                                <span>Online school</span>
                            </div>

                            <div class="hero-title fill-text">
                                <a href="/projects/domznaniy" class="d-inline-block effect-ajax" data-dsn-ajax="next">
                                    <h2 class="title">DOMZNANIY</h2>
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
        <!-- ========== End Next Project  ========== -->

    </div>


</main>


